history.content:
Don't know if this is the best place to post this but I figured it was worth a shot.

Would love to hear from people who've taken CS294-043 (Visual Object and Activity Recognition) with Professors Efros and Darrell and also from those who've taken CS294-131 (Special Topics in Deep Learning) with Professors Song and Darrell. Would especially love to hear about how cutting-edge/accessible the content is and about the workload.

On a more logistical note, how many units are these courses? Looked around in a couple places and couldn't seem to find a clear answer.
history.subject: Thoughts on CS294-043 and CS294-131?
